%Docstring
Returns the path to the height texture map.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setHeightTexturePath`
%End

    double parallaxScale() const;
%Docstring
Returns the parallax scale, which dictates the strength of the height
displacement effect.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setParallaxScale`

.. seealso:: :py:func:`heightTexturePath`
%End

    QString emissionTexturePath() const;
%Docstring
Returns the path to the emission/luminosity texture map.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`emissionFactor`

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setEmissionTexturePath`
%End

    double emissionFactor() const;
%Docstring
Returns the emission factor, which dictates the strength of the emission
effect.

A value of 1.0 indicates that the emission texture values should be used
directly. Larger values result in more light emission.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setEmissionFactor`

.. seealso:: :py:func:`emissionTexturePath`
%End

    QString ambientOcclusionTexturePath() const;
%Docstring
Returns the path to the ambient occlusion texture map.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setAmbientOcclusionTexturePath`
%End

    double textureScale() const;
%Docstring
Returns the texture scale.

The texture scale changes the size of the displayed texture in the 3D
scene. If the texture scale is less than 1, the texture will be
stretched.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setTextureScale`
%End

    double textureRotation() const;
%Docstring
Returns the texture rotation, in degrees.

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setTextureRotation`
%End

    double opacity() const;
%Docstring
Returns the opacity of the surface

.. seealso:: :py:func:`setOpacity`

.. versionadded:: 4.2
%End

